windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 1033 to 1071?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
C) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
options.C: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

windows.answer: C) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 874 to 894?
A) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
B) Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
options.B: Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
